Class DefaultLexer

java.lang.Object
  com.floreysoft.jmte.guts.DefaultLexer
All Implemented Interfaces:
Lexer
public class DefaultLexer
extends java.lang.Object
implements Lexer

Default implementation for lexer. You are invited to subclass it if you want extended behavior of script sections. One possible way would be to first check for your extended input and if it does not match simply delegate to the super implementation.

You are also free to implement it from scratch.

nextToken

public Token nextToken(java.lang.String input,
                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> model,
                       boolean skipMode,
                       ErrorHandler errorHandler)
Description copied from interface: Lexer
Scans and expands the input to find out what kind of token a certain script section represents.

Specified by:
nextToken in interface Lexer
Parameters:
input - the script section to be parsed
model - the complete model possibly containing temporary data
skipMode - true if no expressions shall be evaluated while parsing - this is both for performance and even safety as in this mode some variables might remain unset which would be set in non-skip mode
errorHandler - handler to issue error messages and warnings
Returns:
implementation of Token to indicate the type of section that was parsed
